# ─── Public (embedded in the browser bundle; not secrets) ───
# Create a project at https://supabase.com → Settings → API
# Use the Project URL and the anon (public) key. RLS in Supabase protects your data.

# Canonical origin for Astro `site`, sitemap, Open Graph (optional — defaults to www in astro.config.mjs).
# PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.wellnessfirstglobal.com
PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://zcxlsqimyuaxcuersdyv.supabase.co
PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Optional — CI/build only (never expose to the browser).
# Lets Astro prerender `/resources/[slug]` shells for member / webinar / paid rows during `astro build`.
# Without it, anon RLS only returns `access_level=public`, so non-public resource routes may not generate.
# Same key lets `/webinars` and `/webinars/[slug]` include member-only webinar shells at build time.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# Optional — webinar confirmation Edge Function URL (Supabase).
# POST `{ "booking_id": "<uuid>" }` with `Authorization: Bearer <user access_token>`.
# Example: https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co/functions/v1/send-webinar-confirmation
# Unset = dev placeholder: client sets `confirmation_sent_at` after RSVP.
# The Edge Function sends email and updates `confirmation_sent_at`; never expose `service_role` in frontend env.
# PUBLIC_WEBINAR_BOOKING_NOTIFY_URL=

# Optional — internal ping after a member submits `/my-wellness-space/consultation` (new rows only).
# POST `{ "request_id": "<uuid>" }` with optional `Authorization: Bearer <user access_token>` if your endpoint expects it.
# No secrets belong in PUBLIC_* — implement verification server-side only.
# PUBLIC_CONSULTATION_NOTIFY_URL=

# Comma-separated Supabase user emails allowed to open /app/cms/* (hub + read-only lists).
# Empty = no one can access the hub; the Decap editor at /admin/ still uses its own GitHub OAuth.
# PUBLIC_CMS_ALLOWED_EMAILS=editor@example.com,other@example.com

# ─── Decap CMS on Vercel (production /admin login) ───
# Add these only in the Vercel project (server secrets — do not prefix with PUBLIC_):
# OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=...
# OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → OAuth Apps → Authorization callback URL:
#   Must match your Decap base_url host + /callback, e.g. https://wellnessfirstglobal.vercel.app/callback

# Copy to ".env" for local dev: cp .env.example .env
# Cloudflare Pages: set the same variable names in Project → Settings → Environment variables
# (build + production). Rebuild after changing; values are baked into client JS at build time for PUBLIC_*.

# Supabase Auth (dashboard): set Site URL to your production origin (e.g. https://www.wellnessfirstglobal.com)
# and add redirect URLs: http://localhost:4321/** and your production /app/** if using email links.

# ─── Public forms (contact, newsletter/interest, webinar interest) ───
# PUBLIC_FORM_MODE=mailto   → always mailto handoff.
# PUBLIC_FORM_MODE=api      → POST /api/* (needs Cloudflare Pages Functions `functions/` or your own routes).
#
# When unset (see src/lib/forms-config.ts):
#   - Vercel production build → mailto (no /functions on Vercel by default).
#   - Cloudflare production → API.
#   - astro dev → mailto (plain dev server has no /api).
#
# Cloudflare Pages: bind an optional KV namespace as FORM_KV to persist submissions (JSON per key).
# Project → Settings → Functions → KV namespace bindings → Variable name: FORM_KV
# Without KV, submissions still return 200 OK; only a short log line is written (no PII in logs).
# Test /api/* on a Preview or Production URL; local `wrangler pages dev` can conflict with the Astro
# + Cloudflare adapter output—use the dashboard build or a branch preview for end-to-end checks.
